	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=2117&amp;mid=110743386237641">Mana robe RULES!</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=2117&amp;mid=110743386237641#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Thu, Feb 3rd 7:31 AM 2005</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=347958"><span id=" ">EQfiends</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">13 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Ok.. I dont understand why people like to dis the mana robe.&nbsp;&nbsp;Even if it had NEGATIVE stats it would argueably be the best robe in the game.  People go gaga over a FT3 item.. but then look at mana robe.. FT40 when used (3 second cast 60hp for 20mana with zero recast = FT40).  And to boot most higher chars have FT maxed anyway.  Plus with regen the way it is losing 60 hp wont even make you bat an eyelash.  Plus chanters can eat the life out of their DS hehe.  <br/><br/>Think about it.. how many times is 100-200 hp going to save your ass on a mob that hits for 1000+  I would much rather have the extra mana so I can mez it ;)</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
