	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=275738"><span id=" ">evercrackanonymous</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">10 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.50]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>ok, this robe is a good robe. BUT there are down sides to it. <br/>1st: its stats suck<br/>2nd: it takes 60hp and gives 20m(low mana return)<br/>3rd: if you land a good nuke or dot with low life<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;   (50% or less) you WILL get agro and most<br/>     likely die(unless you have a healer watching<br/>     everyone close)<br/>I would only recomend this for a necro, reason being is that you can have your hp to mana convert spell on and right click this bad boy. Then you cast your lifetap dot to help start the fight(low chance on getting agro). While the dot is doing its thing, you start clicking the robe more, and more, and more, and well...you get the picture. When your at 50 or 60% life, use you best lifetap for your level and heal yourself(if done properly you will not get agro if in a group the mob should be low on life by that time). Or if soloing start fight with darkness, normal dots and then a fear. After you fear cast the lifetap dot and then start clicking the robe.<br/>This will make you very self sufficient.<br/>I love my robe, i use it for my mage and my necro but like a said, if your low on life and land a good nuke your out of the game(it happened a few times with my mage when i first got it.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
